Now I know how my
parents used to feel.

03:30.444 --> 03:32.444
So exciting, fun.

03:34.448 --> 03:36.415
CHIP: Now you're learning
that rifle a bit, aren't you?

03:36.450 --> 03:37.783
CAROL: We got eight.

03:37.818 --> 03:39.985
CHIP: Whoa.
There's number nine.

03:42.690 --> 03:44.456
Good job.

03:44.491 --> 03:47.693
We haven't even made it
a mile down this channel yet,
and we're getting plenty.

03:47.962 --> 03:49.928
I think we're gonna do
pretty good tonight.

03:50.030 --> 03:52.497
We just got a long
night ahead of us.

03:55.336 --> 03:57.502
MARTHA MAE: As far as
waste goes, I guess that
comes full circle with

03:57.538 --> 03:59.304
everything that we have.

03:59.340 --> 04:01.306
Whatever we can use,
we'll utilize it...

04:01.325 --> 04:03.508
So nothing goes to waste.

04:16.557 --> 04:18.223
